str2: A command, charge, injunction; a precept, rule of living. From paraggello; a mandate.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.
To teach, direct, admonish. A prolonged form of a primary verb dao; to teach.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Name, character, fame, reputation. From a presumed derivative of the base of ginosko; a 'name'.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: (a) I say, speak; I mean, mention, tell, (b) I call, name, especially in the pass., (c) I tell, command.

parse: Verb - Perfect Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.
Of Hebrew origin; Hierusalem, the capitol of Palestine.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Teaching, doctrine, what is taught. From didasko; instruction.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To will, intend, desire, wish. Middle voice of a primary verb; to 'will, ' i.e. be willing.
To bring upon; meet: I cause to be imputed to. From epi and ago; to superinduce, i.e. Inflict, charge.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
Blood, literally, figuratively or specially; by implication, bloodshed, also kindred.
